Rpgen vendors PLINK 2's pgenlib library and genotype format-import closure as
third-party C++ source, built into a static library (src/libPLINK2.a, produced
at install time by src/Makevars) and exposed through Rpgen's own C-callable
API. This file documents what was vendored, from where, and under what
license.

Why Rpgen is GPL-3 (not GPL (>= 2) like the rest of this monorepo)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
pgenlib is licensed LGPL (>= 3): GNU Lesser General Public License, version
3 or later. Combining LGPL-3 code into a single work is only
license-compatible up through GPL version 3 (the LGPL-3 "combined work"
permission is written against GPLv3's terms, not GPLv2's). Rpgen statically
links pgenlib into one shared object, so it is licensed GPL-3, not the
GPL (>= 2) used by the other packages in this monorepo (Rfmalloc, Rggml,
Rgguf, Rllm), none of which vendor any LGPL code.

