Immediate vendoring source
---------------------------
pgenlib's sources here were not copied directly from the chrchang/plink-ng
repository. They are generated by the project's own vendoring recipe,
../../tools/vendor-pgenlib/ (see its PROVENANCE.md), from a pinned,
immutable CRAN source tarball of the R package 'pgenlibr'
(https://github.com/chrchang/plink-ng, maintained by Christopher Chang,
LGPL (>= 3) licensed), which already vendors exactly the pgenlib *read*
subset plus zstd, libdeflate and simde, and builds them into libPLINK2.a
for CRAN. Specifically:

    configure, configure.ac              = (SHA-pinned pgenlibr 0.6.2 CRAN tarball), verbatim
    cleanup                              = generated base plus vendored-object cleanup
    src/Makevars.ucrt                    = (same tarball), verbatim
    src/Makevars.in, src/Makevars.win    = generated base plus Rpgen import/shim wiring
    tools/*_version.cpp                  = (same tarball), verbatim
    tools/include/**                     = (same tarball), verbatim, entire subtree

`Rscript tools/vendor-pgenlib/vendorpgen.R check` re-derives the base manifest
and asserts it still equals this recipe. Makevars carry the additional
hand-maintained importer shim described by the second recipe below.

What was vendored
-------------------
Under tools/include/ (built into src/libPLINK2.a):

  pgenlib / plink2 core (tools/include/include/), the pgenlib *read* path
  only - no writer:
    pgenlib_ffi_support.cc/.h, pgenlib_misc.cc/.h, pgenlib_read.cc/.h,
    plink2_base.cc/.h, plink2_bits.cc/.h, plink2_bgzf.cc/.h,
    plink2_float.cc/.h, plink2_htable.cc/.h, plink2_memory.cc/.h,
    plink2_simd.cc/.h, plink2_string.cc/.h, plink2_text.cc/.h,
    plink2_thread.cc/.h, plink2_zstfile.cc/.h, pvar_ffi_support.cc/.h
  Bundled Zstd 1.5.5 (tools/include/zstd/), BSD licensed, used for
    compressed .pvar/.pgen auxiliary reads.
  Bundled libdeflate (tools/include/libdeflate/), MIT licensed, used for
    gzip/zlib-compressed auxiliary reads.
  Bundled SIMDe (tools/include/simde/), MIT licensed, portable SIMD
    intrinsics shims pgenlib's own vectorized code is written against.

  pgenlibr's Rcpp-facing pvar.cpp/pvar.h, pgenlibr.cpp, and RcppExports.cpp
  are not vendored. Rpgen talks to pgenlib through R's plain C API and does
  not declare or require Rcpp. See PROVENANCE.md.

Not present in the pgenlibr-derived subset:
  pgenlib's variant *writer* (PgenWriter and friends) is not part of the
  pgenlibr 0.6.2 vendored subset. pgenlib_write.cc/.h is supplied by the
  second recipe below because PLINK 2's format importers require it.

PLINK 2's genotype format-import closure
----------------------------------------
Rpgen calls PLINK 2's own format importers rather than maintaining separate
parsers. This closure is vendored from a second, independent source, plink-ng
itself at a pinned commit, rather than the pgenlibr tarball above.

Upstream project (same project as pgenlib above, different subset)
  plink-ng, https://github.com/chrchang/plink-ng
  Copyright (C) 2005-2026 Shaun Purcell, Christopher Chang.
  Commit a81e38220b16e3907bdcedbe6ce39b273e001e13, fetched as GitHub's
  per-commit tarball, SHA256-pinned in
  ../../tools/vendor-plink2-import/vendorplink2import.R (see that tool's
  PROVENANCE.md for the full file list, why each file is needed, and how the
  closure was verified to compile+link by actually building it).
  License: plink2's *program* code (as opposed to the pgenlib *library* code
  above) is GNU General Public License, version 3 or later - see "Verbatim
  upstream GPL-3 notice" below. This is a second, independently-licensed
  vendored component, distinct from pgenlib's LGPL (>= 3) license (see "Why
  Rpgen is GPL-3" above) - both are compatible with Rpgen's own GPL-3.

  `Rscript tools/vendor-plink2-import/vendorplink2import.R check` re-derives
  this subset and asserts it still equals the recipe.

What was vendored (built into src/libPLINK2.a alongside the pgenlib read
subset above):

  Program-level plink2 sources (tools/include/, GPL-3 - note: NOT under
  tools/include/include/, since plink2's program files #include each other
  without an "include/" prefix - see the vendoring tool's PROVENANCE.md):
    plink2_import.cc/.h (VcfToPgen(), BcfToPgen(), OxGenToPgen(),
    OxBgenToPgen(), OxHapslegendToPgen(), Plink1DosageToPgen(),
    EigfileToPgen()), plink2_common.cc/.h,
    plink2_cmdline.cc/.h (patched, see below), plink2_pvar.cc/.h,
    plink2_psam.cc/.h, plink2_compress_stream.cc/.h,
    plink2_import_legacy.cc/.h (PedmapToPgen(), TpedToPgen()),
    plink2_random.cc/.h, plink2_decompress.cc/.h, plink2_data.cc/.h,
    plink2_family.cc/.h.

  Library-level additions (tools/include/include/, joining the pgenlib read
  subset above):
    pgenlib_write.cc/.h - the .pgen writer VcfToPgen() calls. LGPL (>= 3),
      same license and upstream notice as the read subset above. A local
      compile-time hook redirects decoded writer records during direct
      Rfmalloc ingestion; ordinary file-producing imports remain upstream.
    SFMT.c/.h - the SIMD-oriented Fast Mersenne Twister PRNG
      plink2_random.h wraps. BSD-3-Clause (Mutsuo Saito, Makoto Matsumoto,
      Hiroshima University, University of Tokyo) - see "Verbatim upstream
      BSD-3-Clause notice (SFMT)" below.

  Local patches:
    tools/vendor-plink2-import/patches/pgenlib_write_direct_sink.patch adds
    the optional terminal record hook described above. The hook glue in
    src/rpgen_direct_sink.cpp/.h is Rpgen code under GPL-3.

    tools/vendor-plink2-import/patches/plink2_cmdline.cc.patch
    replaces plink2_cmdline.cc's logputs_silent()/logputs()/logerrputs()/
    logputsb()/logerrputsb() to route through R's Rprintf()/REprintf()
    instead of a log FILE*/stdout/stderr - required, not cosmetic: Rpgen
    never opens a log file, so upstream's version (which unconditionally
    fputs()s to it) would segfault. During direct ingestion it also reports
    record transfer instead of falsely claiming that a PGEN was written; see
    that tool's PROVENANCE.md for the full rationale.

Rpgen's own code
------------------
src/rpgen.cpp and src/rpgen_import.cpp (the C-callable implementations and
R_init_Rpgen registration), inst/include/Rpgen.h (the installed C-callable
header for downstream LinkingTo consumers), and all R/ code are Rpgen's own,
GPL-3 licensed, as declared in DESCRIPTION.

